# Code owners — review required for the supply-chain attack surface (§4.9).
#
# These globs cover dependency manifests, their committed lockfiles, the CI
# workflows, and every enforcement control. The point is that a risky change
# (a new dependency, a base-image bump) and the control that would catch a bad
# one (a lockfile hash, a vuln gate, an Action pin) cannot be changed together
# in a single unreviewed PR.
#
# Owner review only has teeth when branch protection requires it — see
# docs/repository_governance.md.

# ── Python dependencies + hashed lockfile ────────────────────────────────────
/backend/requirements.txt           @Badry-Kudu
/backend/requirements.lock          @Badry-Kudu
/backend/requirements-oracle.txt    @Badry-Kudu

# ── Frontend dependencies + lockfile ─────────────────────────────────────────
/frontend/package.json              @Badry-Kudu
/frontend/package-lock.json         @Badry-Kudu

# ── CI/CD workflows and supply-chain enforcement config ──────────────────────
/.github/workflows/                 @Badry-Kudu
/.github/dependabot.yml             @Badry-Kudu
/.github/CODEOWNERS                 @Badry-Kudu
/scripts/check_action_pins.py       @Badry-Kudu

# ── Container build definitions + digest-pinned base images ──────────────────
/docker/                            @Badry-Kudu
